    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="sga" resp="#HAM2001">
                <ab>
                     <lb n="1" style="text-direction:verticle"/><expan><w lemma="oróit" corresp="http://www.dil.ie/33938"><abbr><hi rend="ligature">O<hi rend="supraline">R</hi></hi></abbr><ex>ÓIT</ex></w></expan>
                     <w lemma="do" corresp="http://www.dil.ie/17096">DO</w>
                    <persName><name nymRef="Dúnchad" corresp="www.dil.ie/19240">DUNCHAD</name></persName> 
                    <lb n="2"/><foreign xml:lang="la"><w lemma="presbiter"><expan><abbr><hi rend="supraline">P</hi></abbr><ex>RE</ex></expan>SPI<expan><abbr><hi rend="supraline">T</hi></abbr><ex>ER</ex></expan></w></foreign> <w lemma="bec" corresp="http://www.dil.ie/5512">BIC</w>
                  </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
  <app loc="1">
   <note>Read by <ref source="#PET1845">Petrie (1878, 74)</ref> as OROIT DO DUNCHAD PRESPITER HIC.</note>
  </app>
 </listApp>                
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <p>A prayer for Dunchad, the little priest.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary"> 
                <list type="witDetail">
                    <item n="1"><p><q>The reference to Dunchad's position as priest is most unusual in an Irish inscription, and so is the epithet BIC, though it appears in the <ref target="https://emili.celt.dias.ie/ARM-002">Kilnasaggart inscription</ref>. The use of P rather than B (presbiter) is quite common in Hiberno-Latin, but the use of the Latin word in an otherwise Irish inscription is not</q> (<ref source="#HAM2001">Hamlin 2001, 58</ref>).</p></item>
                    <item n="2"><p>It is perhaps indicative of a later Old Irish date that here we find dative <hi rend="italic">bic</hi> (of o, ā-stem adjective <ref target="https://dil.ie/5512"><hi rend="italic">becc</hi></ref> 'small, little') rather than earlier <hi rend="italic">biuc</hi>.</p></item>
                        </list>
            </div>
